    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Payment Methods\n Processing Payments\n Getting Started With Electronic Payments\n Payment Gateways\n Payment Runs\n Make Payments with the Payment Center\n Self-Service Payment Pages\n Lightning Platform Payment Sites for Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Hosted Card Payments in Experience Cloud Sites...\n Set Up the Hosted Card Payments Component\n Add the Hosted Card Payments Component to an Experience Cloud Site\n Add the Hosted Card Payments Component to a Lightning Page\n Guidelines for the Hosted Card Payments Component\n Permissions for the Hosted Card Payments Component\n Managing Gateway Transaction Responses\n Locked and Unlocked Invoices\n Payment Allocations\n Issuing Credits\n Creating Debits and Add-on Charges\n Applying Refunds\n Payment Data Model\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nSet Up the Hosted Card Payments Component\n\nWhen you add the Hosted Card Payments Component to Experience Cloud sites and Lightning pages, you give your customers and partners a safe and convenient way to make payments and store credit card information.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Salesforce Billing Winter ’20 and later\nIMPORTANT Before you can access the Hosted Card Payments component in the Experience Builder or Lightning App Builder, a developer must embed the force:CardPayment code in a wrapper component. For developer instructions on coding and configuring the component, read Hosted Card Payments Lightning Component.\n\nThe Hosted Card Payments component requires an active Enable Billing HPP Component setting in Salesforce Billing. If your org doesn’t have this setting enabled, contact Salesforce Tier 3 Support.\n\nAdd the Hosted Card Payments Component to an Experience Cloud Site\nAfter a developer configures the Hosted Card Payments component, add the component to an Experience Cloud site. Then, customers and partners can submit payments and save credit information through the site.\nAdd the Hosted Card Payments Component to a Lightning Page\nAfter a developer configures the Hosted Card Payments component, add the component to a Lightning page. Then, customers and partners can submit payments and save credit information through the page.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
